Discover Scenic Scotland
This spring, let American Airlines introduce you to
Scotland with our new service to Glasgow -city of
culture, history, and festivals.
Glasgow has more to offer than you
ever dreamed... with its restored
Victorian architecture to the vast city
GLASGOW
parks and museums. Or play golf
where the game began in nearby
American Airlines
St. Andrews - all set amidst some of
the most beautiful scenery in Western Europe. And
American Airlines can take you there with daily non-
stop service from Chicago beginning May 15, 1990.
Now American Airlines can take you to more
of Europe than ever before with more than 140
flights per week to 11 cities in 8 countries. And
no matter where your trip begins, American and
American Eagle®, our regional airline associate,
provide an expansive network of flights which allow
you to conveniently connect to your international
flight in a city that's on the way - not out of the way.
On each of our European flights, you'll receive the
extra care and attention of American's Interna-
tional Flagship Service. And American Airlines
Fly Away Vacations™ - backed by our exclusive
warranty - are designed to make your vacation
what it should be: fun, flexible, and affordable.
Glasgow is a city that loves to be visited. Call
American Airlines and let us take you there.
For reservations and information, call your Travel
Agent or American Airlines at (800) 433-7300.
AmericanAirlines
